C({"name": "validate", "params": {"options": {"description": "", "type": "", "optional": false, "order": 0, "name": "options"}, "type": {"description": "", "type": "", "optional": false, "order": 1, "name": "type"}}, "ret": {"type": "undefined", "description": ""}, "type": "function", "comment": "<p>subscriber: validate</p>\n\n<p>Adds support for the jQuery validation rulesets.\nFor types: <text>, <password>, <textarea>, <radio>, <checkbox> sets up rules through rules(\"add\", rules) for validation plugin\nFor type <form> sets up as options object for validate method of validation plugin\nFor rules of types <checkboxes> and <radiobuttons> you should use this subscriber for type <form> (to see example below)</p>\n\n<p>Example:\nvalidations for radiobuttons group and for text field:</p>\n\n<p>(start code)\n{\n\"type\" : \"form\",\n    \"validate\" :\n{\n    \"rules\" :\n    {\n        \"radio<em>group\": \"required\"\n    }\n},\n\"elements\" :\n[\n    {\n        \"type\" : \"radiobuttons\",\n        \"caption\" : \"You should choose from here\"\n        \"name\" : \"radio</em>group\",\n        \"options\" :\n        {\n            \"Y\" : \"Yes\",\n            \"N\" : \"No\"\n        }</p>\n\n<pre><code>},\n{\n    \"type\" : \"text\",\n    \"name\" : \"url\",\n    \"validate\" :\n    {\n        \"required\" : true,\n        \"url\" : true\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>]\n}\n(end)</p>", "src": "src/dform.extensions.js", "line": 510, "children": []})